scout bungaloo is a good creature  beacuse if it is attacked u can discard it adding its energy plus 2 to anohter creature, which basically wastes an opponents attack. jungertrug of course is all offense. zayas bow is helpful if u have sawgrass and/or pody. use binding when u have a creature that is strong but cant attack, like yajo unless u wanna keep usi his power. if u uSE another binding, use it on the same creature of yours so u only have one bound creature. stealth is good cause u basically get to attack before damage is done, and then you attack. use sheath on a guy that you used binding on so it stays alive longer to keep your opponent inactive. pretty much everything else is slef explainatory i hope u enjoy this deck!   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
